<!-- ═══ HERO ═══ -->
<div class="hero fade-in" id="hero">
  <div class="day-pill">Day 02 — Phase 1 — Week 1</div>
  <h1 class="hero-title">TypeScript:<br><span class="accent">Async</span> Patterns<br>& the <span class="accent2">Real World</span></h1>
  <p class="hero-lead">Day 1 gave you the type system foundations. Today you take TypeScript into the code you actually ship — async functions that can fail, APIs that lie, environment configs that break, and Express servers that need to know who's calling. This is where TypeScript pays its rent.</p>
  <div class="hero-tags">
    <span class="tag t">Result Pattern</span>
    <span class="tag p">Typed Fetch</span>
    <span class="tag g">tsconfig Mastery</span>
    <span class="tag r">Express Typing</span>
    <span class="tag gr">Env Variables</span>
    <span class="tag t">satisfies Operator</span>
  </div>
