      <div class="res-card-desc">Matt's take on the Result pattern and why try/catch fails TypeScript. 18 minutes. Watch it after completing this doc — reinforces everything in Section 1.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="res-card" href="https://kentcdodds.com/blog/get-a-catch-block-error-message-with-typescript" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <div class="res-card-type" style="color:var(--teal);">📝 Article</div>
      <div class="res-card-name">Catch Block Error Message with TypeScript</div>
      <div class="res-card-desc">Kent C. Dodds on the exact problem of catch (e: unknown). Short, focused, directly relevant. Shows you the utility function pattern for narrowing caught errors cleanly.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="res-card" href="https://www.totaltypescript.com/tsconfig-cheat-sheet" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <div class="res-card-type" style="color:var(--green);">📋 Cheatsheet</div>
      <div class="res-card-name">Total TypeScript — TSConfig Cheat Sheet</div>
      <div class="res-card-desc">Matt Pocock's recommended tsconfig for every scenario: library, Next.js, Node.js. The definitive reference. Bookmark and use instead of copying from random Stack Overflow answers.</div>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

